nd the\nstate pays no more than it wants\nto pay. Our defense budget of\n$15,000.000 000 would correspond\nif a mathematical parallel\nj could be established between the\njtwo systems -to less than $2,000\n1000,000 in the Soviet Union\nSky Is the Limit\nThe fact is that we are dras\ntically limited In our expenditures,\nwhile the sky is the limit in a\ntotalitarian regime, where nothing\nbelongs to the Individual, but\neverything is controlled by a hand\nful of autocratic rulers.\nFive years ago Americans\nstormed the beaches of Normandy\nat a high cost In human life They\nfought, recklessly and brilliantly,\nthe powerful army of a totalita\nrian regime and with less than\none year from D day they\nmanaged to crush Hitler's legions\nNow\u2014five years later\u2014our own\nsecurity, and possibly the Ameri\ncan way of life, is threatened even\nmore than in the two wars in\nwhich we Joined to save democ\nracy on the other side of the\nAtlantic.\nIn their eagerness to crush those\nwho advocated totalitarianism, our\npolicy-makers overlooked one\nfundamental factor Democracy,\nlike religion, cannot be paid mere\nlip service It must be in the\nhearts of those who advocate it.\nIt must not be simply a dressing\nfor speechless and official declara\ntions.\nDuring the honeymoon between\nthe U. 8 8. R and the We\u00bbt\u2014a\nhoneymoon which started gaily\nafter one ruthless dictator Hiller\nattacked his confederate. (Kalin\u2014\nwe accepted the outward aigns\nthat Russia was fighting with us\nfor the sake of democracy\nWe allowed a handful of men\n\u2014who for personal or Ideological\nreasons had become enamored of\nCommunist doctrines to roam\nthe country and extol not only\nthe magnificent combat power of\nthe Russians, but also the hon\nesty of purpose of the Russian\nleaders, who differed from the\nNazis only Ui their Oriental ap\nproach to totalitarianism\nOur lop Government official*\nclosed their eyes to the subversives\nwho infiltrated our political life\nheesure 